how to teach you baby to sleep in the crib my baby is months old she loves sleeping in her bouncer and swing she sleeps more in her bouncer then in her crib once i put in her crib she is awake what can i do my son was the same way what they like is the way they feel secure lying in the swing and bouncer as compared to lying flat on their backs although because of the risk of sids its advised to place them on their back my son would never sleep on his back i was so scared and worried about him being on his stomach but he just screamed on his back i started trying different things like sleeping on his side with one of those things that wraps around them and keeps them from rolling that seemed the help make him feel secure i didn't start putting him in his crib until he was months old though he slept with me at first because i breast fed and it was easier then i realized uh oh i had better break him of this quick i had to put him in the swing in my room for a week first then move him to the swing in his room for a week then finally he made it into the crib and after several sleepless nights he got it now at months old he is seeming to revert to some sleepless nights good luck and you do what makes you feel the most comfortable Sudden infant death syndrome Breastfeeding Fast bowling Sin City Mattress EastEnders Aerial (dance move) Knots Landing Shaggy dog story Swingout Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Humphrey Bogart Suplex Silent Night, Deadly Night Friends Equine conformation Love and Theft The Amber Spyglass Professional wrestling holds John the Baptist Insomnia The Inside West Coast Swing The Shining (film) Blonde on Blonde Lisa's First Word Nirvana (band) Blood on the Tracks Days of our Lives Jon Secada The Fairly OddParents AFI 100 Years series Avenue Q Out-of-body experience Sleeping Murder Kodocha Sharon Tate The Death Gate Cycle Scenes from a Memory Professional wrestling attacks Professional wrestling throws Characters